      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's exhausting trying to \"create\" meaning when the void is so much more real. people just use your \"searching\" as an excuse to keep the charade going. if everything is just a story we tell ourselves to avoid the truth, why bother telling it? why keep playing a game that has no winner and no prize? it feels like there's no real way out of the exhaustion other than just... stopping the noise.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
